=Create vRouter Interface=
This operation is used to create a vRouter Interface.

==Request==
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Method || POST
|-
|Request URI || 
* XML format
/vtns/{vtn_name}/vrouters/{vrt_name}/interfaces.xml
* JSON format
/vtns/{vtn_name}/vrouters/{vrt_name}/interfaces.json
|-
|Request body ||
* XML format
 <interface if_name="{if_name}" description="{description}" adminstat
  us="{adminstatus}" ipaddr="{ipaddr}" prefix="{prefix}" macaddr="{mac
  addr}" />
* JSON format
 {
   "interface": {
          "if_name": "{if_name}",
          "description": "{description}",
          "adminstatus": "{adminstatus}",
          "ipaddr": "{ipaddr}",
          "prefix": "{prefix}",
          "macaddr": "{macaddr}"
    }
  }
|}


===Description of request URI elements===
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Element || Description || Required
|-
|vtn_name || VTN name.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters that can include
alphabets, numbers, and underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|-
|vrt_name || vRouter name.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters that can include
alphabets, numbers, and underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|}

===Description of request elements===
{|class = "wikitable"
|-
|Element || Description || Required
|-
|if_name || vRouter Interface name.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters that can include
alphabets, numbers, and underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|-
|description || Additional information.
Valid value: A string of up to 127 characters.
||No
|-
|adminstatus || Admin status.
Valid value: enable, disable.
||No
|-
|ipaddr || IPv4 address.
Valid value: IPv4 dot-separated format.
Example: 192.168.1.1
Note: The value of this parameter must be unique
within vRouter
||No
|-
|prefix ||Prefix length.
Valid value: A positive integer.
Valid range: 1 - 30.
Note: This parameter is required if ipaddr is specified.
||No
|-
|macaddr || The MAC address.
Valid value: Three groups of four hexadecimal digits
separated by dots (.).
Example: 0123.4567.89ab
Note: MAC address is case insensitive.
||No
|}

*[Important]
:When the type of controller specified in controller_id is pfc, adminstatus of vRouter Interface connot be
specified.

===Response Body===
:None


